rComments: Has been a great mentor and I loved hearing about all of her stories from work. Has a calm teaching style, a great sense of humour and makes everyone feel relaxed.
A great experience, she was really helpful. Project was a lot of work. Wish she was there for all 4 years!

I found her lectures rather painful. Just regurgitated textbook slides, and then when you ask her a question, 50% of the time she will tell you she doesn't know. Also very frustrating to ask her for help, get one answer, and then a couple days/weeks later have her give you the exact opposite answer. The group assignment wasn't bad. Just start early
Pretty easy class..... final project will take a lot of work. Make sure you write clearly and organize your paper well with lots of headings and subheadings (maybe even throw in a table of contents).
